<item>
            <title>[CXF-7114] Disable HTTP TRACE method on CXF http-jetty transport</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7114</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We had a security scan and found that standalone CXF endpoint using http-jetty transport still had HTTP TRACE method enabled. It is considered as a security risk. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not a problem if the CXF http-jetty transport is used with Pax Web as Pax Web had already had it&apos;s embedded Jetty engine&apos;s HTTP TRACE method disabled by default. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So we should disable HTTP TRACE method in JettyHTTPHandler. Please find attached patch.txt for more detail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
